I had been a regular customer of Sal's Pizza, but they officially lost me today.  I ordered a hamburger, a plate of spaghetti an a coke.  A simple order.  When the delivery man arrived, he was incredibly rude, and I was quick to get rid of him.  So quick that I didn't realize he had not delivered The Coke I had been charged for.  I called Sal's, but they not only refused to honor the order, they told me that I was lying and that I never ordered the soda they had charged me for.  Again, I WAS CHARGED FOR IT, so I obviously ordered it.  They called me back a few minutes later, and I thought it was to make amends for the  problem, but as it turns out, they called just to argue with me some more.  I'm finished.  I'll take my business elsewhere from now on.

Quality of pizza has decreased since Sal left. It's obvious. It's been so long, I can't even remember what the real Sal's tasted like. The taste, the crunch, it's all gone. But at least back in the day, the price matched the flavor.  Lower the prices or up the quality! This is coming from someone who used to order weekly. I'll still pick Sal's up every once in a while... Then I regret it all over again.  You can find the same quality pizza for half the price if you're willing to walk 10 minutes.

It's difficult not to be mislead into believing Sal's is just another New York pizza joint. The decor might inspire thoughts of greasy slices and cheap, sugary fountain drinks but under the common exterior is an amazing destination for your Italian food stuff.
